      "content": "The primary endpoint was met with statistical significance, p<0.05, indicating that the observed benefits in cognitive function were not due to chance. This was seen across the entire study population, with an average improvement of 25% in cognitive scores compared to the placebo group. The results were consistent across various subgroups, including age and severity of symptoms, further validating the efficacy of NeuroZest in Phase II.",
      "source": "target",
